    <!-- 1. Purpose -->
    <section id="whsmp-purpose" class="wms-section">
        <h2>1 PURPOSE OF DOCUMENT</h2>
        <h3>PURPOSE</h3>
        <p>This Work Health and Safety Management Plan (WHSMP) has been developed to outline the work health and safety relationship between Franmarine and {{clientName}}. The WHSMP demonstrates Franmarine's ability to exceed all work health and safety requirements whilst working towards our own safety objective of zero injuries.</p>
        <p>The Franmarine Health and Safety Management System is certified by DNV to ISO 45001:2018 Occupational health and safety management systems under the scope of management of diving and integrated underwater services provided to the defence, infrastructure, shipping and oil and gas industries.</p>
        <p>All Diving Operations will be carried out in accordance with AS/NZS 2299.1:2015 Occupational Diving Operations as a minimum, using Surface Supplied Breathing Apparatus.</p>

        <h3>SAFETY OBJECTIVES</h3>
        <p>The aim of Franmarine, through their HSEQ Policies, is to identify, assess and control potential risks and hazards. We believe that injury in the workplace is entirely preventable.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Franmarine has a goal of <strong>zero injuries</strong> for every project</li>
            <li>Franmarine fully supports employees requiring rehabilitation and return to work programs</li>
            <li>All levels of management shall have direct involvement and demonstrate commitment to Health and Safety</li>
            <li>All personnel have duty of care responsibilities related to health and safety</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>FRANMARINE POLICIES</h3>
        <table class="wms-table">
            <tbody>
                <tr><td>FRA-POL-012</td><td>Health & Safety Policy</td></tr>
                <tr><td>FRA-POL-007</td><td>Environmental Policy</td></tr>
                <tr><td>FRA-POL-006</td><td>Quality Policy</td></tr>
                <tr><td>FRA-POL-009</td><td>Rehabilitation and Return to Work Policy</td></tr>
                <tr><td>FRA-POL-011</td><td>Training Policy and Development</td></tr>
                <tr><td>FRA-POL-008</td><td>Fitness for Work Policy</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </section>

    <!-- 2. Project WHS Team -->
