    <!-- 3. Legislation -->
    <section id="whsmp-legislation" class="wms-section page-break-before">
        <h2>3 LEGISLATION & STANDARDS</h2>
        <p>All Franmarine diving operations will conform to all applicable Acts and Regulations, including:</p>
        <table class="wms-table">
            <tbody>
                <tr><td>Work Health and Safety Act 2020 (WA)</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Work Health and Safety (General) Regulations 2022 (WA)</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Environmental Protection Act 1986 (WA)</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Dangerous Goods (Road and Rail transport) Act 2008</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Marine Safety Act 1998</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>STANDARDS</h3>
        <p>All Franmarine operations conducted according to AS/NZS 2299.1:2015 Occupational diving operations, Part 1: Standard operational practice.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. Hazard Identification -->
    <section id="whsmp-hazard" class="wms-section">
        <h2>4 HAZARD IDENTIFICATION & RISK MANAGEMENT</h2>
        <p>Franmarine has procedures in place for the systematic review of health and safety hazards and risk over the life cycle of the diving project.</p>
        <p>When the risk is assessed as high, a Safe Work Method Statement (SWMS) shall be developed. A SWMS must be included with all diving tasks as diving works are designated high risk works.</p>

        <h3>RISK MATRIX</h3>
        <table class="wms-table risk-matrix">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Likelihood</th>
                    <th>Insignificant</th>
                    <th>Minor</th>
                    <th>Moderate</th>
                    <th>Major</th>
                    <th>Catastrophic</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td>Almost Certain</td><td class="risk-high">HIGH</td><td class="risk-high">HIGH</td><td class="risk-extreme">EXTREME</td><td class="risk-extreme">EXTREME</td><td class="risk-extreme">EXTREME</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Likely</td><td class="risk-medium">MEDIUM</td><td class="risk-high">HIGH</td><td class="risk-high">HIGH</td><td class="risk-extreme">EXTREME</td><td class="risk-extreme">EXTREME</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Possible</td><td class="risk-low">LOW</td><td class="risk-medium">MEDIUM</td><td class="risk-high">HIGH</td><td class="risk-high">HIGH</td><td class="risk-extreme">EXTREME</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Unlikely</td><td class="risk-low">LOW</td><td class="risk-low">LOW</td><td class="risk-medium">MEDIUM</td><td class="risk-medium">MEDIUM</td><td class="risk-high">HIGH</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Rare</td><td class="risk-low">LOW</td><td class="risk-low">LOW</td><td class="risk-low">LOW</td><td class="risk-medium">MEDIUM</td><td class="risk-medium">MEDIUM</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>HIERARCHY OF CONTROLS</h3>
        <ol class="hierarchy-list">
            <li><strong>Eliminate</strong> - Remove the hazard completely</li>
            <li><strong>Substitute</strong> - Replace a hazardous process/substance with one which is less hazardous</li>
            <li><strong>Isolation</strong> - Remove the person from the hazardous environment</li>
            <li><strong>Engineering</strong> - Provide physical barriers or engineered modifications</li>
            <li><strong>Administrative</strong> - Establish policies, procedures and work practices</li>
            <li><strong>PPE</strong> - Use equipment that provides protection to individuals</li>
        </ol>

        {{#if hasAdditionalActivities}}
        <h3>ADDITIONAL HIGH RISK ACTIVITIES</h3>
        <p>This project includes the following additional high risk work activities that require specific hazard controls:</p>
        <ul>
            {{#each additionalActivities}}
            <li>{{this}}</li>
            {{/each}}
        </ul>
        <p>Refer to the Safe Work Method Statement (SWMS) for detailed hazard analysis and control measures for these activities.</p>
        {{/if}}
