    <!-- 5. Personnel & Training -->
    <section id="whsmp-personnel" class="wms-section page-break-before">
        <h2>5 PERSONNEL & TRAINING</h2>
        <p>All personnel assigned to this project shall be qualified and experienced as per the Franmarine Diving Operation Manual requirements.</p>

        <h3>AIR DIVING SUPERVISOR QUALIFICATIONS</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>ADAS Part 3 (or equivalent) Diving Supervisor certification</li>
            <li>Current AS/NZS 2299.1 medical fitness certificate</li>
            <li>Current first aid and oxygen administration certifications</li>
            <li>Project-specific inductions as required</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>DIVER QUALIFICATIONS</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>ADAS Part 2 (or equivalent) Occupational Diver certification</li>
            <li>Current AS/NZS 2299.1 medical fitness certificate</li>
            <li>Current first aid certification</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- 6. Daily Operations -->
    <section id="whsmp-operations" class="wms-section">
        <h2>6 DAILY OPERATIONS</h2>

        <h3>TOOLBOX MEETINGS</h3>
        <p>All Supervisors are required to hold "Toolbox" meetings at the start of each shift to discuss current activities, highlighting any hazards and safety matters.</p>

        <h3>FATIGUE MANAGEMENT</h3>
        <p>All employees should monitor themselves and others for signs of fatigue. The Franmarine Fatigue Assessment Checklist HSE-FOR-008 shall be used when concerns arise.</p>

        <h3>ALCOHOL AND DRUGS</h3>
        <p>Franmarine has <strong>zero tolerance</strong> to alcohol and illicit drugs in the workplace. All Employees shall comply with any random drug and alcohol testing.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 7. PPE -->
    <section id="whsmp-ppe" class="wms-section">
        <h2>7 PERSONAL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT</h2>
        <p>Franmarine shall provide the following PPE to all personnel as a minimum:</p>
        <table class="wms-table">
            <thead>
                <tr><th>Equipment</th><th>Standard</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td>Safety Helmet (hard hat)</td><td>AS/NZS 1801</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Safety Glasses</td><td>AS/NZS 1337</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Safety Footwear (steel toe)</td><td>AS/NZS 2210.3</td></tr>
                <tr><td>High Visibility Clothing</td><td>AS/NZS 4602</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Hearing Protection</td><td>AS/NZS 1270</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Safety Gloves</td><td>AS/NZS 2161</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>The minimum on-site requirement is a hard hat, steel toe capped boots and high visibility clothing with reflective strips.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 8. Incident Reporting -->
    <section id="whsmp-incident" class="wms-section">
        <h2>8 INCIDENT REPORTING</h2>
        <p>All incidents, near misses, and hazards must be reported immediately to the Dive Supervisor.</p>
        <p>For full details on Franmarine Accident and Incidents, see Incident and Investigation Procedure HSE-PRO-025.</p>

        <h3>INCIDENT CLASSIFICATION</h3>
        <table class="wms-table">
            <thead>
                <tr><th>Classification</th><th>Description</th><th>Reporting</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
